snippet.title: Sin Cos Tan - Basic Trigonometry  - Working unknown angles
snippet.description:
Trigonometry is an easy way to work out the unknown sides and angles of a right angled triangle. The trick - know the side names - the opposite, hypotenuse, and adjacent, and know how and when to apply the trigonomic functions - sin, cos and tan. this is the only trick to getting it right every time!
In this lesson, students learn work out unknown angles using use sine, cosine, and tangent. You will need a scientific calculator for the problems in this lesson - and I'll show you how to access one on your computer. To donate to the tecmath channel:  https://paypal.me/tecmath?locale.x=en_AU
